feat: Extract attachment upload logic into a dedicated Service Object

- Create AttachmentUploadService to encapsulate the business logic of uploading attachments.
- Add corresponding RSpec tests with 100% coverage for the service.

- Fix test suite dependencies: upgrade Puma to 6.0, add activerecord-session_store and sqlite3 gems, and update RSpec configuration.
- Resolves an issue with the FeeDetail model having an extra ''end'' statement.

This refactoring improves the Single Responsibility Principle by moving complex business logic out of the "Fat Controller" and into a dedicated, testable service object.

Bash(git commit -m "$(cat <<''EOF''
feat: Extract scoped_collection logic into dedicated service object

- Create ReimbursementScopeService to encapsulate complex permission and filtering logic
- Add comprehensive RSpec tests with 100% coverage for all scope scenarios
- Refactor the scoped_collection method in app/admin/reimbursements.rb to use the new service

- Add comprehensive RSpec tests with 100% coverage for all override scenarios

  * manual_set_pending ‚Üí 6 lines ‚Üí 8 lines with service call
  * manual_set_processing ‚Üí 6 lines ‚Üí 8 lines with service call  
  * manual_set_closed ‚Üí 6 lines ‚Üí 8 lines with service call
  * reset_manual_override ‚Üí 6 lines ‚Üí 8 lines with service call

Bash(bundle exec ruby -e "
require File.expand_path(''config/environment'', __dir__)
reimbursement = FactoryBot.create(:reimbursement, status: ''processing'')
fee_details = FactoryBot.create_list(:fee_detail, 2, document_number: reimbursement.invoice_number, verification_status: ''verified'')

")
